description: Once again Fearless Dawn gets herself into a predicament! Following a treasure map to find a secret elixir, Fearless Dawn travels deep within a murky swamp. Ignoring the warnings of Old Lady Flannigan, and hot on the trail of buried pirate booty, Fearless Dawn and her sidekick, 'The Masked Kid' get assaulted by the giant swamp creature!

volume.name: Fearless Dawn: The Secret of the Swamp

description:
Since 1996, Finder has set the bar for science-fiction storytelling, with a lush, intricate world and compelling characters. Now, Dark Horse is proud to present four more story arcs of Carla Speed McNeil's groundbreaking series in a single, affordably priced volume!

This second of two Finder Library volumes collects the multiple Eisner Award-nominated story arcs Dream Sequence, Mystery Date, The Rescuers, and Five Crazy Women.
name: Dream Sequence; Mystery Date; The Rescuers; Five Crazy Women

description:
Dark Heritage

Marvin has very vivid nightmares. His dreams are haunted by a powerful and charismatic, faceless figure. Trapped in the horrifying surreal world, Marvin has to find a way out, by facing his own demons The journey takes him from the darkest corners of his past, to the uncertain future. Seeking redemption, Marvin has a chance to save someone's life. However, nothing comes without a price...

Reversible

Dr Nicolas has the power of changing people's fate. Ironically all the happiness he brings to their lives doesn't prevent his own from being bitter and sad. To understand the importance of forgiveness he must face the horror of destroying someone's future. What he doesn't know is that someone is already watching that future. There is nothing irreversible for the faceless man...
name: Dark Heritage; Reversible

volume.name: The Further Fattening Adventures of Pudge, Girl Blimp

description: A mysterious plane crash claims the life of Jonny Zero's parents and leaves him critically injured. Enter Professor Zero, Jonny's uncle, who uses his experimental robotic nonplasm to rebuild the boy. Jonny is transformed into Go Boy 7, the human action machine!This collection of the first four issues of the series feature flash-fire action and high sci-fi drama. Written by Tom Peyer (The Authority), with kinetic art by hot newcomer Jon Sommariva. Don't let Go Boy 7 pass you by!
name: Volume 1

description: The painting of Mata Hari gets stolen again. A new revealing secret connected to the painting brings the family Kiekeboe to Bretagne. There they find a real treasure.
name: De Schat Van Mata Hari

description: Brussels gets startled by two peculiar incidents: 1) those who get beamed by Manneken Pis loses his hair and 2) the mysterios sect of the Haar-Tisten sells the hair growing potion Krollemboll. Ofcourse one has to do with the other and Marcel Kiekeboe gets involved in both.
name: De Haar-Tisten

description: It's not going well with the African republic Boeloe Boeloe (see also 'De dorpstiran van Boeloe Boeloe'). President Mose Mombakka needs money urgently and meanwhile soldier Bib Pralin Gaga crown himself the Sun King of the republic. Luckily Mose, Kiekeboe and the kidnapped Charlotte get help from the American toy manufacturer Blinky Toys.
name: De Zwarte Zonnekoning

description: The Scottish meteorologist Douglas Mac Reel can influence the weather by playing an ingenious bagpipe with a specially composed melody. That invention suits the mad scientist Timotheus Triangl very well. He steals the melody and kidnaps Fanny. Kiekeboe starts the pursuit.
name: De Doedelzak Van Mac Reel
Nella Buona e Nella Cattiva Sorte

description: Martin Mystre is visited by two bizarre masked people who ask him to investigate about the strange disappearance of one of their companions: they are the Real life Superheroes, common people who love to dress as superheroes. A seemingly harmless game, that risks to become a tragedy, after somebody murdered one of them. Between fiction and fact, dream and reality, Martin's investigation will go straight to the mysterious base of Elsewhere, and then towards an impossible and enchanted land, full of dangers and populated by strange characters, such as the Detective of the Impossible never met! To complete this year's Almanacco, full-color dossiers about the wonderful world of Oz, the dream explorers and Alejandro Jodorowsky, the psycho-magician, and an overview of mysterious books, movies, TV series and videogames of the year.
name: Almanacco del Mistero 2013

description:
A very special issue: 256 full-color pages to remember the writer, the publisher, the traveller and the dreamer. A heartfel celebration through the books, the comics, the movies, the music he loved, along with the tales of his adventurous places: the Amazonas, Africa, the American West... Also, a long dossier on Mister No and the reprint for the first time in Technicolor of a classic story featuring the ironic Brazilian pilot. The volume is completed by some gags of "Mister Bo", the funny alter-ego of Sergio Bonelli.

Special issue dedicated to Sergio Bonelli.
name: Almanacco dell'Avventura 2013

description: A teenager named Colby Reynolds feels disconnected from the world around him, until a mysterious girl literally falls into his life, and starts him on an adventure he'll never forget!
name: Chapter 1: Impact

volume.name: Makeshift Miracle: The Girl From Nowhere
